<p><strong>Staff of Loss</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Glintstone Staffs" href="/Glintstone+Staffs">Glintstone Staff</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Staff of Loss</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a>,&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Intelligence" href="/Intelligence" target="">Intelligence</a> and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for those looking to play an ambusher type of caster.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Staff missing its glintstone. Wielded by sorcerers who believe that discovery comes through acts of asceticism.</em></p> 
 <p><em>This staff only distinguishes itself when casting invisibility sorceries, but that is reason enough for some to wield it.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Staff of Loss in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Staff of Loss weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Sellia, Town of Sorcery" href="/Sellia,+Town+of+Sorcery">Sellia, Town of Sorcery</a>:&nbsp;Found on a corpse leaning over a building's balcony in the west. Accessible by jumping across the rooftops. See the Sellia page for details on how to get it. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive map?id=3223&amp;lat=-175.804687&amp;lng=147.434242&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+map?id=3223&amp;lat=-175.804687&amp;lng=147.434242&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Elden Ring Map here</a>]</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Staff of Loss Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: This armament has no skill. If the armament in the other hand has a skill, that skill will be used instead.</li> 
 <li>This weapon can be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a></li> 
 <li><strong>Staff of Loss</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stones" href="/Smithing+Stones" target="">Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>Despite the description, this staff does not block the casting of non-Invisibility spells.</li> 
 <li>Boosts&nbsp;attack power&nbsp;of Invisibility sorceries by 30%.<br> 
  <ul> 
   <li>Invisibility sorceries include <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Night Shard" href="/Night+Shard" target="">Night Shard</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Night Comet" href="/Night+Comet" target="">Night Comet</a>. Also note that night sorceries are not dodged by NPC characters, making this an excellent staff to fight enemies that tend to dodge other ranged attacks</li> 
   <li>As of Patch 1.03.2, this 30% damage buff will be applied to appropriate spells regardless if it is the staff being used to cast. It only needs to be visibly equipped on the player character to apply.</li> 
   <li>Despite seeming like they belong in the category of Invisibility, the following sorceries do not have increased damage or duration according to testing: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ambush Shard" href="/Ambush+Shard" target="">Ambush Shard</a><span style="color: #828282;">, </span><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Night Maiden's Mist" href="/Night+Maiden's+Mist" target="">Night Maiden's Mist</a>, and&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Eternal Darkness" href="/Eternal+Darkness" target="">Eternal Darkness</a>.</li> 
   <li>Despite being categorized as sorceries of invisibility internally, the following sorceries are unaffected because they do not deal damage: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Unseen Blade" href="/Unseen+Blade">Unseen Blade</a>&nbsp;and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Unseen Form" href="/Unseen+Form">Unseen Form</a>.</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>With 80 INT, this staff has:&nbsp;179 sorcery scaling at +0 //&nbsp;339 sorcery scaling at +25</li> 
 <li>At ~80&nbsp;INT, this staff will outperform any staff in the game in terms of raw damage, so long as you limit yourself to only night sorceries (which is quite limiting).</li> 
 <li>Using 2 staffs simultaneously will cause the 30% boost to stack multiplicatively, creating the highest boost that can be attained for a single magic school (Gravity sorceries can be boosted similarly, but lack the ability to upgrade the staff) 
  <ul> 
   <li>This can only be done in NG+ or by getting someone to drop the second staff for you, as only one can be obtained per playthrough</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>This staff has the same handle as the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Carian Glintblade Staff" href="/Carian+Glintblade+Staff">Carian Glintblade Staff</a>, though it's a different color, and lacks a glintstone (or perhaps, it is just invisible).</li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;200 <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Runes" href="/Runes">Runes</a></li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
