				<li id="16610915" class="cmnt-root" data="71" data-d="1649683895000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578955/Staff-of-Loss" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">11 Apr 2022 09:31</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16610915" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">If you wield two of these at 80 int, your effective spell buff for Night Comet and Night Shard will be 572. If you were to use one of these and Lusat&apos;s in your other hand, you will be doing 536 on the spells. In the scenario where you commit to using these two spells, it is incredibly worth using two of them, and will have the best sorcery dps in the game, bar none. Incredibly underrated staff, and I could see more people speccing into using just these for the sheer damage in the future. If you wanted to push the damage even further, you could tack on the sorcery boost talismans. With the 8% version, you will be hitting 617 spell buff, and if you add the 4% version on top you will hit 641. Adding Magic Scorpion and assuming pvp will be another 8% netting you to 692. If you drink a physick with magic damage, you will reach another 15%, putting you at 795. If you were to stand in a Terra Magica, you will get another 35%, putting you at 1073. Even with all these buffs, we can still go further, having a buff from Golden Vow, adding another 7.5% giving you 1153. Now, there is one final buff, a cooperator using Commander&apos;s Standard, to yield a final 20% increase, giving you a total spell buff of 1383. One thing I forgot to mention is that since these stack multiplicatively, I wasn&apos;t keeping the decimals in and dropped them for each increase, so 1383 is a little under the true total value. At the end of all of this, is it really feasible? No, but it is fun to theory craft and see how potentially busted this staff can be with these spells, and I think I was able to paint a good picture of how potentially busted it can be. There is no doubt that you can realistically hit 692 consistently though, which might draw your attention.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16610915" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16610915" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">3</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>72</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>1</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16610915"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16610915" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16610915"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
